text: yeah it looks like you will still have to search your contacts to see who qualifies for what list but I will check this out, thanks for  the link!
Idea: Allow Forms to be able to be expired. This way you can create forms that are only available from X -> Y date. Like an event registration form.
Would it have a fallback so that you wouldn’t have a landing page with no form?
yea the form portion would expire and you could add a text area for some kind of communicaion on it

as for the page itself, if the form/page were tied together you could always just expire the page, but expiring just the registration form would allow users to still see the form and for the creator to be able to set something and forget it in way
idea: a form that can only be used for X times, after that switch to another form. is like the date expiring idea.

would be nice if there was a way to manually force expire the cache for URL’s. I have a situation where I updated all of the pages on a site, and a handful are showing with screwed up styles because of it.
when i use cachebuster the pages are working as intended
